Readings: Patch Management

Patch management is a software or even a code that improves an installed program. When there is a security flaw discovered or a programâ€™s functionality needs to be improved, then software developers create a patch to address these aspects. These patches can be categorized into three different categories, feature updates, bug fixes, and security updates. Feature updates improve the software functionality and provide additional capabilities. Bug fixes address certain errors found in software, that help it run smoothly and prevent crashes. Security patches enhance security by correcting known software vulnerabilities and covering holes in your systems, which prevent malicious actors from exploiting the flaws and compromising your organization. A good patch management is a crucial aspect when it comes to maintaining the security, 
